<p class="MsoNormalM"><span>The Hampta Pass trek is truly special, amagnificent, otherworldly, and naturally beautiful place blessed by God.<span>&nbsp; </span>It features mountains, waterfalls, rivers,meadows, and a variety of Himalayan medicinal plants and flowers. The vibrantcolors of the landscape and its location in the lap of the Himalayas, near thebeautiful town of Manali, are major attractions.<span>&nbsp; </span>During this journey, you'll constantly findyourself thinking, "Hamta Pass is one of the best treks in theHimalayas!"<br /></span></p>
<p><b><span style="font-size: 16pt; line-height: 22.8267px">Hampta Pass Trek: Where Scenic Beauty Meets Adventure</span></b></p>
<p style=" text-align: justify"><span>Hampta Pass Trek in Himachal Pradesh is a very ancient trekking route. The trek journey starts from our Manali town. Hampta Pass Trek is known for its popularity, cultural heritage, and being one of the oldest trekking routes. Thousands of people from all over India and abroad visit here every year for the Hampta Pass Trek. The special popularity of the Hampta Pass Trek lies in the fact that this trek starts from the beautiful city of Manali in Himachal Pradesh. As you know, Manali is considered one of the most favorite cities for tourists, where people from every corner of India come to visit this city. It is a base camp from where many trekking routes originate, such as Bhrigu Lake, Beas Kund Trek, Spiti Valley Trek, Leh Ladakh Bike Trek, and many other trekking routes. <br /><br />Manali is the most important base camp for all these trekking routes.<span>&nbsp;<span>&nbsp;</span></span>Many other trekking routes at high altitude levels, such as Pin Parvati Pass, Pin Bhaba Pass, and Pin Panjal Valley, also have Manali as their starting point.<span>&nbsp;<span>&nbsp;</span></span>Similarly, Hampta Pass is also a 04 nights 5-day trek that you can do from Manali to Manali. This trek is known for its beautiful natural beauty, rivers, waterfalls, and high mountains, forest, which make this trekking route special. During this trek, the river flowing from Hampta Pass, meadows, waterfalls, lakes, and snow-covered mountains make this trek even more attractive, drawing tourists towards it. <br /><br />Therefore, Hampta Pass is a trek with immense popularity. Hampta Pass Trek is a monsoon trek, whose season runs from June to September for 4 months. Trekking here during this time is very easy and peaceful. If you want to spend a very peaceful time, then Hampta Pass is one of the most special treks in India, which you can make a memorable trek with Himalayan Hikers.</span></p>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
<meta name="ProgId" content="Word.DocumentW" />
<meta name="Generator" content="Microsoft Word 15" />
<meta name="Originator" content="Microsoft Word 15" />
