<p class="MsoNormalM"><b><span style="font-size:18.0pt;line-height:107%">6 Things We Love About the Hampta pass Chandratal Trek.</span></b></p>
<p style="text-indent:-18.0pt"><span><span>1.<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span>The Hampta Pass trek in Indiais a circular trek that starts from Manali, goes through Chikka, Balu ka Ghera,Hampta pass, Shes Geru, and Chandratal, and then returns to Manali via the AtalTunnel and Rohtang Pass. This journey is amazing, incredible, and beautiful.</span></p>
<p style="text-indent:-18.0pt"><span><span>2.<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span>Did you know that when we startthe Hampta Pass trek, this amazing journey and incredible adventure beginsright from Manali? The Himalayas will always captivate you on this trek. Assoon as you start this journey from Manali, the amazing forests and vegetation,and the Himalayan animals found there, will draw you in.<span>&nbsp; </span>Adding to the allure of this trek are the icywinds and pure environment emanating from Hampta Pass, and the pure, coldwater, which makes this trek an easy, wonderful, and unforgettable experiencefor you</span></p>
<p style="text-indent:-18.0pt"><span><span>3.<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span>The Hampta Pass, along withChandratal Lake, embodies the unique culture of Lahaul and Spiti.<span>&nbsp; </span>Our ancestors used this pass for trade andherding livestock between Lahaul, Spiti, and Leh-Ladakh.<span>&nbsp; </span>In those times, before roads existed, peoplefrom Manali and the surrounding areas used this route for personal travel andto transport goods and animals.<span>&nbsp; </span>Importand export of goods were carried out along this Trek, which has now emerged asa beautiful trekking route. What makes this journey special is the localculture, the interactions between the people, and the rivers and waterfallsoriginating from the Himalayan ranges, making this trek a truly memorableexperience.</span></p>
<p style="text-indent:-18.0pt"><span><span>4.<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span>A special feature of this trekis that in the Hampta Pass area, from June to July, August, and September, youcan have a unique experience of seeing many Himalayan flowers along thetrekking route. This trek features wild flowers found in the high Himalayas,which are particularly captivating. I have observed that when people come onthis trekking route and walk amidst these beautiful flowers, a unique smileappears on their faces, and the experience of witnessing nature provides aspecial sense of peace and tranquility within them, which is the highlight ofthis trek.</span></p>
<p style="text-indent:-18.0pt"><span><span>5.<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span>A special highlight of theChandratal lake. Have you ever wondered why it's called Chandratal? Chandratalmeans a beautiful natural lake shaped like a crescent moon. It's a masterpieceof nature, located at an altitude of approximately 14,000 feet in theLahaul-Spiti Valley. To reach it, you have to travel about 75 kilometers byroad from Chatru after completing the Hampta Pass trek. Chandratal is trulyamazing; it's as if some divine power created this natural lake. Thiscrescent-shaped lake attracts tourists with its stunning beauty. It's situatedamidst azure waters and beautiful snow-capped mountains, and experiencing thislake along with the Hampta Pass trek is an unforgettable experience. It offersa unique experience for tourists.</span></p>
<p style="text-indent:-18.0pt"><span><span>6.<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span>After completing the Hamptapass &amp; Chandratal trek, when we leave our last camp with the Chatru Camp forManali on Day 5, there's a special highlight on the way – the Rohtang Pass andAtal Tunnel. You'll be happy to know that along with Hampta Pass andChandratal, you can also enjoy the views of the Atal Tunnel and Rohtang Pass onthis trek. Many people from all over the country come specifically to see theRohtang Pass and Atal Tunnel, but you are fortunate to have the opportunity toexperience Hampta Pass, Chandratal, and the Rohtang-Atal Tunnel on this trek,which adds immense value to your 5-day journey.<span>&nbsp;</span>As you arrive in Manali, you carry with you an image of natural beautyand the mountains, rivers, streams, vegetation, and wildlife created by God, amemory that will always be cherished as one of the special moments in your lifewhenever you think of the Himalayas.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormalM"><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta name="ProgId" content="Word.DocumentW" /><meta name="Generator" content="Microsoft Word 15" /><meta name="Originator" content="Microsoft Word 15" /><link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:/Users/hp/AppData/Local/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_filelist.xml" /><xml>    </xml><link rel="themeData" href="file:///C:/Users/hp/AppData/Local/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_themedata.thmx" /><link rel="colorSchemeMapping" href="file:///C:/Users/hp/AppData/Local/Temp/msohtmlclip1/01/clip_colorschememapping.xml" /><xml>   </xml></p>
<p class="MsoNormalM"><b><span style="font-size:16.0pt;line-height:107%">Kye Point About the Hampta Pass Chandratal Trek</span></b></p>
<p class="MsoNormalM"><span>This 4-night, 5-day trip will include a29-kilometer trek on foot, including the Hampta Pass and Chandratal, and theremaining approximately 260 kilometers will be covered by vehicle.<span>&nbsp; </span>We will be doing this trek </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormalM"><span><span>&nbsp;</span>Onthe Hampta Pass trek, we start from the town of Manali at an altitude ofapproximately 2000 meters, and the summit point, known as Hampta Pass, is ataround 14,300 feet.<span>&nbsp; </span>We will also reachChandratal Lake at an altitude of approximately 14,000 feet.<span>&nbsp; </span>We will gain significant altitude during thistrek, so it is essential to be physically and mentally fit to make this trekenjoyable and memorable.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormalM"><span>my personal experience regarding the HamptaPass trek. It depends on the child's age, ideally at least 8 to 10 years old,and also on their fitness level.<span>&nbsp; </span>Peopleup to 60 years old can easily complete this trek if they are reasonably fit. Ifyour fitness level is good and you are physically and mentally healthy, thenyou are suitable for this trek.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormalM"><span>As a responsible company, we advise you tothoroughly research any company before booking your trek.<span>&nbsp; </span>Trekking, especially in challenging terrain,is not easy and can be risky.<span>&nbsp; </span>Bookingwith a company that lacks experience, qualified guides, proper campingfacilities, and good cooks can ruin your trek. Therefore, always book your trekwith an experienced trekking company that will make your experience memorable </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormalM"><span>Bring all the necessary equipment for thetrek as advised by Himalayan Hikers. If you don't have any of the requiredtrekking gear, you can easily rent it from Himalayan Hikers; it will beavailable at their base camp in Manali.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormalM"><b><span style="font-size:16.0pt;line-height:107%"></span></b></p>
