                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>What is the duration of the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>The Hampta Pass trek typically takes 5-6 days, including travel time to and from Manali<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>What is the difficulty level of the trek?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>The trek is considered moderate. It involves some steep ascents and descents, river crossings, and traversing over snow, making it suitable for trekkers with a reasonable level of physical fitness.<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
                                                            <div class="detailfaq-item">
                                 <button class="detailfaq-question">
                                 <span>What is the altitude of the Hampta Pass?</span>
                                 <span class="detailfaq-icon">▼</span>
                                 </button>
                                 <div class="detailfaq-answer">
                                    <p>&nbsp;The highest point of the trek is Hampta Pass, which is at an altitude of approximately 4,270 meters (14,009 feet).<br /></p>                                 </div>
                              </div>
